SIMPLE: punitive
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Punitive
<hw>Pu"ni*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to
punishment; involving, awarding, or inflicting punishment; <as>as,
<ex>punitive</ex> law or justice</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If death be <qex>punitive</qex>, so, likewise, is the necessity
imposed upon man of toiling for his subsistence.</q> <rj><qau> I.
Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We shall dread a blow from the <qex>punitive</qex> hand.</q>
<rj><qau>Bagehot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Punitory</ent>⟦br⟧
